@lantern
#end
:touch
#play tcfg
A dead man's lantern lies in the mud, its
oil long spent. His grip still clutches it.
He was trying to leave. He did not.
#end
    end

    stat at 47,19 element Object cycle 3 p1 cp437:0x0F under Empty color 0x07
    oop
@bones
#end
:touch
#play tfc-c
Bones bleached white by a hundred years of
rain. The teeth marks are not from wolves.
The way back was long since forgotten.
#end
    end

    stat at 29,22 element Object cycle 3 p1 cp437:0x02 under Empty color 0x07
    oop
@stormsign
#end
:touch
#play tcefg
The wind claws at your cloak. Thunder cracks
over the towers of Castle Ravenmoor.
Above the shattered gate, letters carved deep:
$ ABANDON WARMTH, YE WHO KNOCK.
The great hall lies to the north. The gate
behind you groaned shut the moment you passed.
There is only one way now: inward.
#end
    end
  end
end

