    stat at 41,9 element Object cycle 3 p1 cp437:0x0C under Empty color 0x00
    oop
@ashelf
#end
:touch
#play tcd
A shelf of rotting genealogies. One spine
reads: RAVENMOOR, an Accounting of the Line.
The pages crumble at your touch, but a slip
of parchment flutters out.
It reads: "The BRASS KEY sleeps where the
family sleeps -- beneath the last portrait,
in the pool of dead light."
#end
    end

    stat at 18,15 element Object cycle 3 p1 cp437:0x9E under Empty color 0x00
    oop
@candelabra
#end
:touch
#play fs
A tarnished brass candelabra, its candles
long guttered to grey stubs. It gives no
light. "Dead light," you murmur, recalling
the clue -- but there is no portrait here.
#end
    end

    stat at 30,20 element Object cycle 2 p1 cp437:0xF0 under Empty color 0x00
    oop
@portrait
#end
:touch
#play t-ecd
The last portrait: a pale lord in a high
collar, eyes following you across the room.
Below him, a plaque -- "HERE SLEEPS THE LINE."
A shaft of dead-grey daylight pools at your
feet. You kneel, pry a loose flagstone, and
lift out a heavy BRASS KEY, warm as a pulse.
#play cdefgab+c
#give gems 1
The library groans. Somewhere north, the
armory latch releases.
#zap touch
#end
:touch
The flagstone is already lifted. Only the
lord's painted stare remains, and it does
not approve of your rummaging.
#end
    end
  end
end

