Rows of broken pews, splintered inward,
as though the congregation clawed toward
the door and never reached it.
#end
    end

    stat at 16,23 element Object cycle 3 p1 cp437:0x3F under Empty color 0x00
    oop
@riddle
#end
:touch
#play tfe
A verse is chiselled into the flagstones,
half-worn by centuries of dripping water:
$-- THE CHAPEL RIDDLE --
I have no throat, yet I can drown a king.
I have no fist, yet break the strongest ring.
I bless the born and wash away the dead.
The cold thing fears me. Carry me instead.
!answer;Speak the answer aloud;
#end
:answer
#play tcefg+c
You whisper: WATER.
The flagstone sinks with a grinding sigh,
and dark steps spiral down into the crypt.
#set riddlesolved
#end
    end
  end
end

