@keeper
#end
:touch
#play tc-c+c
A shape unfolds from the pitch, tall and
thin, and its voice is dry as tomb dust.
So. Another warm thing wanders my dark.
!ask;Who are you?
!stake;I've come for the stake.
!leave;(say nothing)
#end
:ask
I am the Keeper of the Stake. I hold the
one thing that can end the Lord upstairs.
Fools guard treasure. I guard mercy.
#zap touch
:touch
#play tf
The Keeper waits, patient as stone.
!stake;Give me the stake.
!leave;(back away)
#end
:stake
#play tcegtceg
You have walked the whole black spiral and
come out sane. That is proof enough.
The Keeper presses a splinter of ancient
oak into your palm. It is warm.
#give ammo 5
Now go. Put out the long candle.
#zap touch
#zap ask
#zap stake
#change Object Empty
#die
:leave
#play tec
As you like. The dark keeps its counsel.
#end
    end
    stat at 59,2 element Passage cycle 0 p3 board "Vampire's Throne" under Empty color 0x00
  end
end

